{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"92a74d3a-49d3-4a90-b4a5-37dd44dff16a","content":"The issue is clear. In F#, **file order matters** — files can only reference modules defined in files listed *above* them in the `.fsproj`. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFixing the compilation order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_Zihrh6eQzHbxVF8e0Dkzp2","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-18fad64e88c846d9b602cf21fe59861d/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-18fad64e88c846d9b602cf21fe59861d/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"74c56112-6c92-4bf6-944e-08229e322da1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference modules/types defined in files that appear *before* them in the compilation order. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` (listed first - opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`)\n2. `Domain.fs` (listed second - defines the types that Services needs)\n3. `Program.fs` (listed third - uses both)\n\n`Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` (it has `open BrokenOrder.Domain`), but `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs` in the project file. \n\nThe solution is straightforward - I need to move `Domain.fs` before `Services.fs` so the type definitions are available when the services file compiles.","outputTokens":526,"requestId":"F03B:8224F:25D9C13:29DD3D7:69F93E2A"},"id":"af1a3a17-0a34-4832-a005-e9d8460c4f8d","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:47:48.579Z","parentId":"4bd9d7f4-f8f6-494c-8875-7f473c914e47"}
